    <h1>Daily Meditation - June 14</h1>
<h2>Scripture</h2>
<p>And I am convinced that nothing can ever separate us from God's love. Neither
death nor life, neither angels nor demons, neither our fears for today nor our
worries about tomorrow — not even the powers of hell can separate us from God's
love. </p>
<p>No  power in the sky above or in the earth below — indeed, nothing in all 
creation will ever be able to separate us from the love of God that is  revealed
in Christ Jesus our Lord.</p>
<p>Romans 8:38</p>
<h2>Prayer</h2>
<p>There is no power in the universe that is greater than you.  Yet, I often lose
sight of that reality.  When I am frightened and anxious, remind me of your
goodness and allow me to celebrate all that you have done for me.</p>
    

